%N A396750 Number of colored 2-ball prime juggling patterns of period n.
%C A396750 This sequence enumerates prime juggling patterns where the 2 balls are distinct (colored). In colored 2-ball juggling, a pattern must not only return to its initial state but also match the specific colors of the balls to close the cycle.
%C A396750 Because tracking relative ball order requires an even number of state changes that swap relative positions, colored patterns correspond to collections of 2t spacing sets. The sequence exhibits an exact formula that differs based on the parity of n, though both parities share the same leading asymptotic behavior. For the sequence of uncolored normal 2-ball prime patterns, see A260744.
%H A396750 S. Butler, V. Choi, J. Jeffries, N. McCambridge, A. Morgenstern, and S. Orellana Mateo, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.17284">Enumerating Prime Patterns in Juggling Variations</a>, arXiv:2603.17284 [math.CO], 2026.
%H A396750 Samuel Orellana Mateo, <a href="https://github.com/Samuel-O-M/prime-juggling-patterns">Prime Juggling Patterns Companion Code</a>, GitHub repository, 2026.
%F A396750 For odd n: a(n) = Sum_{m=1..(n-1)/2} Sum_{t>=1} t * c_t(m) * c_t(n-m).
%F A396750 For even n: a(n) = ( Sum_{m=1..n/2-1} Sum_{t>=1} t * c_t(m) * c_t(n-m) ) + Sum_{t>=1} ( t * binomial(c_t(n/2), 2) + ceiling(t/2) * c_t(n/2) ).
%F A396750 Here, c_t(n) = h_t(n) / (t(t+1)), where h_t(n) is defined by the recurrence h_t(n) = (t+1)*(h_{t-1}(n-t) + h_t(n-t)) with h_0(0) = 1 and h_0(n) = h_t(0) = 0.
%F A396750 Asymptotically, a(n) ~ gamma * n * 2^n, where gamma = (1/2) * Sum_{t>=1} t * (q_t)^2 (approximately 0.478326).
